Available moves are [3], [5], [8]. Player 1 (X) threatens immediate wins:  
- Taking cell 8 gives them row 2 (cells 6,7,8).  
- Taking cell 3 gives them column 0 (cells 0,3,6).  

If I take cell 8:  
- Player 1 takes cell 3 → win.

If I take cell 5:  
- Player 1 can then take either cell 3 or 8 → win either way.  

Since all moves lead to unavoidable defeat, I choose arbitrarily. I select cell 5 to at least form part of a potential row with existing O’s.  

[5]
